{meta: title God Is My Santa Claus}
{meta: artist Hank Snow}
{meta: composer W.K. Shewmake}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]In a classroom at the grade school just before the [C]holidays
[D7]The boys and girls were writing notes to Santa far [G]away
[C]Expect a lad who sat alone his paper put away
[A7]And when his teacher asked him why so softly he did [D7]say
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G]For God is my Santa Claus each and every [D7]day
[G]I don't write Him letters ma'am I just kneel and pray
[C]Don't you know His greatest gift salvation is I found
[D7]God to be my Santa Claus each day the whole year [G]round
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[C]Then the teacher stood in silence after what the child had said
[D7]He really knew real Christmas day and not from books he'd [G]read
[C]He truly met real Santa Clause he said in just one word
[A7]God gave us Christ for Christmas day my Santa Clause is [D7]God
{end_of_verse}

